                                    <p class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".2s" style="text-align: justify;">
                                        Tadvanam, the unique Vedic Brahmopasana, is from Kenopanishad of the Samaveda. The four Vedas extol the supreme state of 'Amritanandam', or immortal bliss, with revered language, and provide guidance on attaining this state through various spiritual practices
