                                    <p class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay=".3s" style="text-align: justify;">The Vedas embody the highest ideals and most sublime aspects of human civilization. ‘Among the Vedas, I am the Samaveda’ is what the Bhagawan proclaims in the Gita. The Kenopanishad originates in the Talavakara Brahmana
                                        of the Samaveda. The word 'Tadvanam', synonymous with 'Brahman', along with its ‘Upasana’, or spiritual practices, are elucidated in the fourth chapter of this Upanishad.
